        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When I upgraded to Zend 1.8, a new issue arose. The call to inet_pton() in line 62 fails when attempting to validate \"localhost\". I know the error is suppressed and I can set my error handler to ignore it, but it still seems like it would be a common error to incur. It seems like it would be a better solution to avoid the error entirely since \"localhost\" should be regarded as valid"
